result.execSummary:
The defendant Amy L Baker was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.

records.addlTxt: 10:15 am case called. Defendant Amy L Baker in court.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court goes over motion filed by DA-to vacate PPDA. Statement by DA Blader regarding administrative fee to be paid with no response from defendant. Court questions defendant regarding counsel. Defendant waives right to counsel. Statement by defendant does not have the means to pay the $75.00. DA requests vacature of PPDA. Court finds material breach of agreement and enters JOC upon previously entered plea of NO Contest. Court sentences the defendant to Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. DNA sample and surcharge-right to expunge through DOJ explained. Appeal Rights Given.
Motion hearing on December 27, 2016 at 10:00 am.
State's Motion to Vacate Post Plea Diversion Agreement

Case called @ 2:57 p.m. Defendant Amy L Baker in court.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. DE advised of right to counsel. Voluntary waiver of counsel accepted by the Court. Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant. Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained.  Consequences explained for failure to abide by terms of PPDA. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Plea: Ct 1 - NC.  Court accepts plea and stays JOC.  Court accepts terms and conditions of PPDA.  Matter stayed for a period of 12 months. The court reminds the defendant that bond remains in effect throughout the pendency of the PPDA.
Complete ID process with the Sheriff's Department.

Case Called @ 1:54 PM: Defendant Amy L Baker in court, appearing pro se.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel.  Def wishes to have counsel review the proposed PPDA - if necessary she will retain her own counsel.  Court will proceed with that understanding.  DA argues for $500 Signature Bond w/conditions.  NGP entered by Court.   Plea Hrg Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State and probable cause finding as to each count alleged within the complaint.  Plea hearing scheduled for November 16, 2015 at 03:00 pm.
